<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Dual Turbocharger and Exhaust Tubing - Removal - Disassembly of
        Turbocharger
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="10">
        <title>Disassembly of Turbocharger</title>
        <figure id="f3000313" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj15/j15036.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the turbocharger oil drain tubing bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place turbocharger assembly on workbench, and remove four turbocharger oil drain tubing
                bolts (M6 x 25). Discard both O-rings.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000314" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj15/j15035.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the crossover tube V-band clamp</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the crossover tube V-band clamp.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000315" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj15/j15037.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the crossover tube</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the crossover tube by pulling straight out. A twisting motion may be necessary to
                free the long end of the tube containing the seal.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000316" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj15/j15018.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Crossover tube O-ring seal</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the crossover tube O-ring seal and discard.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Acquire the
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_54.xml" xrefid="E30003C">Turbo Crossover Tube Seal Remover / Installer
                </hotlnk>
                . Place holding fixture component into vise and clamp securely.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place crossover tube into fixture and clamp securely.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000317" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj15/j15014.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing the crossover tube seal removal tool</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the crossover tube seal removal tool.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000318" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj15/j15022.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Crossover tube seal removal tool</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Thread crossover tube seal removal tool into tubing seal.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000319" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj15/j15015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the crossover tube seal</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove crossover tube seal with the aid of a Slide Hammer. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_54.xml" xrefid="E30003C">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000320" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj15/j15016.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Crossover tube seal removed</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Unthread seal from tool and discard.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000321" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj15/j15028.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Turbine housing orientation alignment marks</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using a paint stick or other type of marker, add alignment marks over both high and
                low-pressure turbochargers and turbine mating V-band clamp.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000322" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj15/j15023.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the turbine mating V-band clamp</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the turbine mating V-band clamp.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The boost control actuator is not serviceable at this time. If turbocharger performance
                issues arise resulting from the boost control actuator, replace dual turbocharger assembly. Refer to
                Engine Diagnostics.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
